Video 6 — User Input

Overview:
Python’s input() function allows programs to read user input. Inputs are strings by default, and must often be converted to other types.

Key Concepts:

Type conversion: int(), float()
Interactive programs require validation

Example:

age = int(input("Enter your age: "))
print(f"You are {age} years old")

Practical Insights:

Always validate user input to avoid errors
Makes programs interactive and flexible
